
[1]hesitation

   HESITA'TION, n. A pausing or delay in forming an opinion or commencing
   action; doubt;suspension of opinion or decision, from uncertainty what
   is proper to be decided. When evidence is clear, we may decide without
   hesitation.

   1. A stopping in speech; intermission between words; stammering.
